                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yes, some weak classes do need help. But there is a difference between weak classes and non-specialized classes.  A druid, for example, is a powerful class, but not as specilaized in healing as a cleric is.  A shaman is by no means a weak class.  A monk is a weak class.
<br />

<br />
The goal to real player community is to have these classes be able to fill many roles.  Putting artifical restrictions for non-specialized classes to advance in gears is not the way to go.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
