                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Teremar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
As for group makeup, any time you're pushing your limits you will need to pay attention to what classes you bring. That's not unique to LDoN hards by any means. The fact that some classes are not wanted in LDoN hards is a problem with class balance...........</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
My wife and I and a Paladin in our guild always group together.  The 3 DPS spots are fluid, though some people in our guild join us on a more regular basis than others.  When we first started doing hards we did them with the same 3 DPS and we could BARELY win.  Then we had to start switching people out but we wouldn't do them without a necro (Mind Wrack owns), THEN we were able to do them without a necro, THEN just recently we had our rogue go LD for 90% of the adventure and we still won with essentially only 5 people, then the last night we did hards about a week about we just made an open announcement in guild "looking for 3 DPS for hard dungeon" and we took whoever because we knew it didnt matter any more.  We take any classes - even SK's and warriors as DPS, as long as we have two other true DPS classes.  I like SK's for the mana and hp taps and warriors aren't awful DPS and they won't die if they get aggro.  
<br />

<br />
Any plate tank can tank hards, I wouldn't take a druid into a hard ot heal but some do it and like it, bard/shaman is just as good or better for lower risk than just having an enchanter, though I'd rather have more DPS as opposed to either a bard or shaman.  My point?  Barring a second cleric or a second enchanter just about any class can be considered "dps" because LDoN hards are all about how well you work together, not your equipment and "holy trilogy" group makeup.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/icon_pistoles.gif" alt="icon_pistoles.gif" border="0" />  Moderator of The Runes - <span style="font-weight: bold">AKA Griefer Police</span>!
