<br />
You are taking one idea from person A and a second idea from person B and calling these two people hypocritical because they happen to be on the same, overall, side of an argument. /boggle
<br />

<br />
The first statement is mine. Yes, I feel that 1. the ease of LDoN and 2. the perception that GoD is too hard make it quite difficult to form GoD groups. Can I live with that? Sure. But you better believe I'm going to voice my disinterest when someone suggests a <span style="font-weight: bold">change</span> in the game to make LDoN scale in a way that nothing in EQ ever has before. You are saying I'm trying to force people out of LDoN and I reply that every stage of any progression <span style="font-style: italic">path</span> eventually caps out and forces that person to look elsewhere (this is what makes it a path). This is true for raiders and non-raiders alike. It's what keeps the game fresh. You say I'm trying to force people out of LDoN and I say you're trying to hold them back from GoD, content they are capable of doing once they have aquired ornate and the current LDoN armor. 
<br />

<br />
Never before has better gear been made available in old content. Take the Hate or Droga revamps.. Not only was the gear upgraded, but the mobs were too. People keep talking about a progression <span style="font-style: italic">path</span> via LDoN, but if you can just skip the current LDoN level armor altogether and go right to the EP stuff, that's not a path at all. It's mudflation, really. I like the idea of separate normal and hard points MUCH better. With a system like that people probably wouldn't be able to earn the hard points they need for the EP gear until they have already earned the normal points they need for the current LDoN gear. That's a progression <span style="font-style: italic">path</span> (provided they take into account the ability to sell-back the old armor at 70% thus making the EP-level gear somewhere in the 4,000 point range). It's a boring one IMO, but at least it's a path. Allowing people to do normals for EP gear is the equivalent of simply handing out loot IMO.
<br />

<br />
Now, as for your druid comment. I, for one, would never say that. I take druids to GoD sewers all the time. Druids are capable healers NP. Druids healing are not the reason normal LDoNs are easy. Normal LDoNs are too easy because I can pull carelessly and 'tank' 3 adds without even mezzing if I'm feeling lazy. And *please* don't give me that 'but you're a raider' thing. Again, I am a casual just like you. My gear is much closer to yours than to Nadia's or Vinen's.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">Ariu <span style="font-style: italic">give me /pethold damnit!</span> Vil'Aki</span>
