                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here are some situations on requiring "hard" LDoN points in order to reach higher tier of armors.  When players reach level 70, the current level 63+ normal won't exist for them, and the current hard 63+ will become normal.  So how will you define what goes into the pool of hard LDoN APs?
<br />

<br />
Will some people hang at 65 to grind out a bunch of hard LDoN points in order to attain the new tier of armors?
<br />

<br />
Will people at 70 be stuck in doing a hard 68+ adventure in order to reach the higher tier?
<br />

<br />
If no points in normal count toward higher tier, what is the incentive in doing normal LDoN at 70?
<br />

<br />
What makes one leap in gear so special that we should introduce this barrier?  If we do so, should we not go back and revamp the entire LDoN system?
<br />

<br />
Does this mean we should just can all normal LDoNs?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
