                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Mezrin Kortex wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Unmei you need to accept that <span style="font-weight: bold">some of us like LDoN </span>because it fits into our lifestyles.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
But what do you mean with that lifestyle - 90 minute spurts to play, pretty guaranteed gains/hour (points) as opposed to random drops, no travel?
<br />

<br />
If that's the answer (and those are the advantages LDoN offers by my understanding) then incorporating new instanced point-granting (or guaranteed, predictable drops) content in future expansions would be the answer. Adding restrictions like seperate hard points is similiar to forcing people into other new content so falls under the same solution just without using the later expansions.
<br />

<br />
The alternative seems to be to add another level of gear attainable with farming normal ldons, once or twice per expansion release. But while doing it once now sounds feasible maybe, how long can/should that be kept up? 
<br />
Imagine if LDoN had been out before PoP - we'd have had cries to add parchments/runes first, then to add EP loot, then to add time loot, then qvic loot, next week tacvi loot...and we're still farming normals here remember.
<br />
The people that want to advance move(d) to Hard ldons but it seems to be the minority to me (leaderboard data: hard tops out in the hundredsomething with a few at 200, normal has many over 400 and the highest closing in on 1k). People are farming normals for Ssra level gear, VT level gear, and now that they have that start asking for Ep level gear ... in 4 months they ask for qvic... still farming the same mobs.
<br />

<br />
I dont want LDoN-improvements to be the solution because I do enjoy *new* single group content. Let that be new LDoN style content for the people that enjoy that playstye, no problems there, we're both happy. But I'm very much against just inflating the items and point cost in the existing camps.
<br />

<br />
"Luckily" there's a level increase coming that will change the LDoN game anyway. Either they expand LDoN themes with another level (which would make 65 hards the level 70 normal unless they add extra difficulties) or leave it capped at 65 (which would ruin ldon, imo, bad move).
<br />
Remember GoD is still designed for level 70. They made it easier for knights because they whined loud enough (justified ofc). Enchanters are still screwed because we didnt whine loud enough (mob levels are not properly designed for our lvl65 spell line-up).
<br />
 At level 70 GoD will be fine for grouping people that are coming out of LDoN, extra OoW low-end content will make it even more viable, we are happy that they "listened" and SoE will have sold their expansion.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7110&alt=136431" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jennifer DeGartes</a>, Enchantress of <a href="http://www.vazaelle.dk" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caer Cadarn</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
