                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Here are some situations on requiring "hard" LDoN points in order to reach higher tier of armors. When players reach level 70, the current level 63+ normal won't exist for them, and the current hard 63+ will become normal. So how will you define what goes into the pool of hard LDoN APs?
<br />

<br />
Will some people hang at 65 to grind out a bunch of hard LDoN points in order to attain the new tier of armors?
<br />

<br />
Will people at 70 be stuck in doing a hard 68+ adventure in order to reach the higher tier?
<br />

<br />
If no points in normal count toward higher tier, what is the incentive in doing normal LDoN at 70?
<br />

<br />
What makes one leap in gear so special that we should introduce this barrier? If we do so, should we not go back and revamp the entire LDoN system?
<br />

<br />
Does this mean we should just can all normal LDoNs?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Here's my answers:
<br />

<br />
1) The current 63+ hard is probably not appropriate for everyone that's level 70. They need to make at least a new normal and a new hard.
<br />

<br />
2) If they do add elemental level gear to the current LDoN system, it should be buyable only with points gained in level 70 hards. However, the level 70 hard should be designed for people in Ornate/current LDoN gear, not raid gear. A level 70 "even harder" setting for people in raid gear might be needed, assuming enough raiders still want to do LDoN.
<br />

<br />
3) If you don't have adequate gear for level 70 hards, you get it by doing level 70 normals. Once you have adequate gear for hards, you should lose interest in doing normals.
<br />

<br />
4) You need a certain level of gear to do a certain level of content. And by doing that content, you should get the gear needed to move up to the next level. Allowing people to get elemental quality gear from normal LDoNs is too big a gap between the level of the content and the level of the reward. It's not that the particular level of gear is all that special, it's the gap between it and the difficulty of LDoN normals.
<br />

<br />
All with one big caveat: this is all, in my mind, a quick fix. I'd like to see it implemented, but I'd much rather they create NEW LDoN style adventures (meaning instanced and loot bought with points), with tiers that are not necessarily tied to level, but increase in difficulty, and which give points only usable to buy gear from that tier. That way it's an upgrade path with many steps along the way, not a matter of farming the same thing over and over until you can buy the very best gear.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
