                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/Agree Unmei, Jenn,Teremar and others, and stated much better then I. 
<br />
 
<br />
For the record, I agree that 'non-raiders' should have a path toward EP level gear at some point. For all the reasons stated above, I believe the current LDoN expansion should NOT be that path.  
<br />
 
<br />
I think GoD and OoW will provide that level of gear and that it is/will be attainable by level 65-70 characters equipped in Ornate/LDoN level armor.  I am fairly confident this will be the case.  
<br />
 
<br />
If there <span style="font-style: italic">has to be</span> a LDoN 'style' progression to that gear (I don't think there does, but for the sake of argument lets say there does) then it should be either in OoW or in an LDoN2 type expansion (or 'free zones' added to the current game), and those <span style="font-style: italic">new</span> wayfarer camps should be more difficult (not impossible, but challenging initially for people in Ornate/LDoN1 gear) and it should not allow point carry over from LDoN1.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
