                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Teremar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">1) The current 63+ hard is probably not appropriate for everyone that's level 70. They need to make at least a new normal and a new hard.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
True.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">2) If they do add elemental level gear to the current LDoN system, it should be buyable only with points gained in level 70 hards. However, the level 70 hard should be designed for people in Ornate/current LDoN gear, not raid gear. A level 70 "even harder" setting for people in raid gear might be needed, assuming enough raiders still want to do LDoN.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The cureent hard 63+ hard LDoN can be done with people in Ornate/current LDoN gear.
<br />

<br />
I still don't feel we should add an artificial barrier to EP quality gear in LDoN.  Ornte armor used to be available only to raiders.  Now that barrier has been removed.  The future points to EP armor going the same way.  EP seems to trigger a lot of emotions for people, like a holy cattle that is about to fall to sacrilege, but in all honesty the game evolves, and EP is old hat when you look at new GoD gears.
<br />

<br />
Even GoD will be doable by level 70 people in current 1492 LDoN gear.  I fully expect GoD to no longer require the holy trio when level cap is at 70.
<br />

<br />
To my mind, adding EP armor and new dungeons to LDoN is sheerly for the people who enjoy steady dkp that does not involve loot fights, the variation of paces as we progress through a single-group raid gathering, hunting, victory, and afk break.  It's a play style.
<br />

<br />
If no better gear is provided in LDoN, that playstyle may as well die for most people.  I'm one of the few sticking to LDoN without any upgrades.  I keep making new friends cuz older ones move on to GoD's loot fights, to raid guilds, to quitting EQ.  Those are the 3 progression paths we have now.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
