                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Instead of making 68+ hard doable by ornate/current LDoN gear, I would like to see the new normal 68+ be doable by the current 1492 gear, with the new hard 68+ be doable by the next level of gear. I think that's one reason I really don't see the need to require hard LDoN points.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
So what happens to the people that don't have the 1492 gear? That's the trouble with tieing difficulty to just level. Outside LDoN if your gear is lame, or if you haven't got the ideal group makeup, or whatever, you have the option of going to an easier zone. In LDoN, you get the LDoN for your level no matter what. So the level 68+ normal has to be doable by the vast majority of level 68+ players. They don't have the option of going back to the level 63+ adventures.
<br />

<br />
So the normal has to be on the easy side--doable with fairly mediocre Bazaar gear. That's why jumping straight from there to gear that's comparable to elemental gear is inappropriate. Instead, (if they do what I consider the quick fix) you use the normals to gear up for the hards, and the hards to gear up for GoD and OoW.
<br />

<br />
(It may well be that Ornate/Current LDoN will be good enough for GoD at level 70. But that's an emprical question we're not in a position to answer.)
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
