<br />

<br />
I agree completely with you the normal 68+ adventure have  to be doable by normal bazaar stuff (i.e., ornates).  But they will have 3 extra levels on the people who are 65 right now.  If the current 65 people can manage 68+ normal with their 1492 gear, I have a feeling a bunch of level 68s can handle it in ornates.
<br />

<br />
Of course I'm probably wrong on this.  I'll have to interview tanks extensively to figure out what kind of gears they got in order to tank hard LDoN for me.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_axe.gif" alt="icon_axe.gif" border="0" /> And given how fast the mobs in a hard can pound me into a pancake, I'm beginning to think you are right on this.
<br />

<br />
I think LDoN needs a top tier of dungeons that can keep people tantalized for a long time while they wait for future content.  That's why the hard LDoNs are called "hard".  It's something you try when you feel strong and want to meet extra challenge.  And if your equipment isn't good, well you are looking at hunting normal level stuff--which you can do--till you gain more equipment to become strong enough.  The hard is supposed to be a challenge.
<br />

<br />
Wait, this brings up a point.  Right now there isn't a tier of hard adventure gear for LDoN people to buy, really.  The reward for a hard is just double the points and some drops from the named.  So people have the option of doing normal or hard, and many people are therefore doing normal.  Doing hard becomes sort of empty in the end.  So maybe that's what many people's point here is.  Their point is in giving another tier of gears for the folks who do attempt hard.  I like that.
<br />

<br />
It does call for some sort of revamp to separate the normal and hard pool of AP, though.
<br />

<br />
At this point I think we already have a good general consensus here.   I'm glad to understand a lot of our different opinions actually have roots in what we each thought the nitty gritties were.  When someone spells out his nitty gritty, that's when I see wow we actually feel the same way.
<br />

<br />
[EDIT add: What will you do with the normal AP that's never used once you move into doing hard LDoN?  I really don't wnat to be foreced into buying gadgets with my normal AP just to sell in the bazaar.  One thing I love about LDoN is I don't have to play the bazaar game.]</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
