                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">OMG, this is what we've been talking about all along, Lumudan. LDoN is designed to have the mobs automatically scale up in level according to the level of the group. I have counted on that for all of my discussions that this scaling happens when we get the new level 70 cap. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Thats an assumption though.  And while I would be happy if it turns out to be true, I suspect it wont be.  I think SoE is just begining to realize the monster they created with LDoN in its current form.
<br />

<br />
Think about it.  LDoN was one expansion.  Now to keep the casuals happy, the implication is... we have to raise the level limit and add new content and loot to an old expansion (for free) so they can continue to progress because the gap to the latest expansions is to large (debatable but enough believe it so it might as well be true).
<br />

<br />
Now SoE COULD tie the LDoN expansion in with say OoW, but I dont think they thought that far ahead, I hope to be proved wrong... but just a feeling I get based on a variety of posts made by various devs and such.  If thats true, they are stuck adding free content essentially giving people a free expansion to suit a specific playstyle AND most importantly, they are stuck essentially expanding both LDoN style and RAID style play in every expansion from now till the end to keep all the LDoN'ers happy who feel they are now entitled to everything they paid for in a multi-year old expansion.
<br />

<br />
Everquest has always had a soft cap in gear quality.  You could only get so far then you hit a wall, unless you raided.  You were forced to do more difficult content to get better gear.  I always accepted that LDoN would only get me so far, then I would have to claw and scratch through GoD as best I could, or raid.  Until another expansion came out with suitably balanced content for me.  
<br />

<br />
But I never believed LDoN would be the end all be all of the best non-raid loot from now till the end of Everquest, at least not without paying for more ldon style expansions.
<br />

<br />
Perserr</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
