                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, they created a monster so bad/popular that now they are making an entire new game EQ2 for the instanced zone/single-group crowd.
<br />

<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> I feel for EQ in how they are under pressure to include content for big raids (another monster they created), solo campers, single-group campers, LDoNers new themes.
<br />

<br />
Yes, EQ is under pressure to support all of that now.  If it succeeds, it can be the biggest MMORPG, but it's also difficult to support all the simultaneous prongs of progression on a finite source of development fund. The feuding raiders vs. non-raiders issues are driving hordes of players away, further dwindling that fund.  I suspect EQ is going to focus on raiders, hence the summit.
<br />

<br />
It'll be interesting to watch how the future unfolds.
<br />

<br />
For now though, I'm not too interested in fine steps of design discussion.  SoE hasn't even shown an interest to support LDoN despite hundreds of posts.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /> I have a feeling LDoN points will be extended to future upgrades simply because they just implemented returning LDoN gear for refunds.  Yet Brenlo claims no upgrades are in the plans yet.  Again I wonder how much of this has to do with trying to drive people mad enough to pre-order EQ2.  The future is a bit mysterious, and I do like mysteries.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
