                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">By making LDoNs depend on your level (a mistake in my opinion) SOE has put themselves in a situation where they have to update LDoN every time they raise the level cap, that's true. Hopefully that will help them resist the urge to do it very often.
<br />

<br />
Their other mistake was that they released GoD in a state where you needed elemental gear or better to play in it. So that's when SOE said they would add elemental level gear to LDoN. It was never about making LDoN the one and only place for non-raiders to progress. It was about allowing non-raiders to get the gear to play in GoD.
<br />

<br />
Okay, so GoD's been revamped. MAYBE (and I still regard that argument as unsettled) non-raiders can play in it now. Maybe non-raiders will be able to play in it at level 70. Maybe OoW will have places where non-raiders can get geared up for GoD. So maybe SOE can skip putting better gear in LDoN. But I think it's clear a lot of non-raiders like LDoN, and I hope they'll imitate some of its better features in future expansions--and those new LDoN-style adventures will have better gear just because that's how EQ works.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
