                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's time for my morning round of misconception stomping. First, the big one, from two different people:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">People can camp BoT and sell ornate in the bazaar to buy EP gear. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Now those camps are permacamped by people who are farming plat to buy EP gear.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Okay. HELLO! REALITY CHECK! EP GEAR is -not- DROPPABLE. You can farm whatever you dang well please and it will never get you one WHIT closer to elemental gear.   If elemental gear were droppable, I can guarantee you that this would be a VERY different discussion.  I'm sorry you have issues with bottomfeeders on your server, but it's not because they're "farming plat to get elemental gear".  Yeah, it costs a whole 500 plat + ether bits to make a piece of elemental gear.  I could farm that in an hour by killing the lizards in the feerot for fine steel, for hecks sake.
<br />

<br />
/boggle
<br />

<br />
Next:
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As for your demand for progress, many of the old world EQ zones can be done with gradual progress that is natural and without artificial berrier. Many people hate flagging. Anyone is free to move to GoD zone if they can survive it. I still don't see the point in putting in an artificial requirement for hard LDoN. If people make it to 70, the current hard LDoN will become normal for them, and they can only earn 51 points from it. The current normal by the way won't even exist for them anymore. That in itself is enough, IMHO. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You see, here's the problem.
<br />

<br />
Those "natural" barriers to progress that you mention are also natural barriers to LOOT.   Traditional old zone example (real old):
<br />

<br />
You have entered Lower Guk.
<br />
Now, you can't handle all of lower guk at your current gear level.   But you can do the executioner/sage camp.  So you do.   You get loot and you get XP.    You eventually get more powerful and can move on to Frenzy and eventually Archmage/Lord, where you get better XP and loot as you defeat more challenging content.  No problem.
<br />

<br />
Now the LDoN version:
<br />

<br />
You have entered Deepest Guk.
<br />
You can't handle the hard parts of deepest guk at your current gear level.   But you can do easy/normal ones.  So you do. You get XP and loot.  You get more powerful... and...continue to do normal/Easy LDoNs.  And inspite of the fact that the content never becomes more difficult, you magically get better loot. Still.   NOWHERE ELSE IN THE GAME is this the case, and I don't think it should start now.
<br />

<br />
Okay. With those out of my system.
<br />

<br />
The idea of my only single group upgrade path being LDoN-style makes me cry.  Respawnless dungeons with next to no dynamic factors.  I'm having a hard enough time motivating to do some more LDoNs for 40 hp augs.
<br />

<br />
I miss zones like the revamped Cazic Thule.  I look forward to the day when I never need to set foot in LDoN again.
<br />

<br />
I understand that some people like it.  I only ask that they need to meet some sort of challenge (not currently provided by normal LDoN)  (Just the fact that some people are saying "I still need to mez in normal LDoN" is proof enough. WTF?  You should -need- to mez in any content that has a chance in HELL of giving you an upgrade.) and the time investment should be comparable to what it takes for an "honest" raider (not one who has been farming Time for 6 months and no longer needs the gear) to get it.  That means, again, going back my original math, that the new "gear" itself needs to cost somewhere around 5000 points, and the augs should be another 4-5k (Total, not each).  That's roughly commesurate with the time invested by a raider who has just broken into the elementals and is forced to share loot with ~50 other people in their guild.  Yes, there are other benefits to being elementally flagged,  but there are other benefits to LDoN too (Inherent point system. Small, managable chunks, and whatever the heck else you people love about it so much.).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
